n most modern European languages. This was the name of the mother of John the Baptist (Luke 1:60). Etymologically, the name means ‘God is my oath’, and is therefore identical with <i>Elisheba</i>, the name of the wife of Aaron according to the genealogy at Exodus 6:23. The final element seems to have been altered by association with Hebrew <i>shabbāth</i> ‘Sabbath’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Elizabeth Troutbeck had at least 1 son and 2 daughters with Robert Knollys. She was buried in Bishopsgate, London, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"–":"Surnud","1449–Male":"1449–Surnud","1478–1527":"1478–1527","1479–1501":"1479–1501","1481–1521":"1481–1521","–Female":"Surnud","1479":"1479","1501":"1501","1478":"1478","1521":"1521","1481":"1481","1527":"1527","1449":"1449","Bishopsgate, London, England, United Kingdom":"Bishopsgate, London, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Hampshire, England":"Hampshire, England","England":"England","North Mymms, Hertfordshire, England":"North Mymms, Hertfordshire, England"},"fi":{"–":"Kuollut","1449–Male":"1449–Kuollut","1478–1527":"1478–1527","1479–1501":"1479–1501","1481–1521":"1481–1521","–Female":"Kuollut","1479":"1479","1501":"1501","1478":"1478","1521":"1521","1481":"1481","1527":"1527","1449":"1449","Bishopsgate, London, England, United Kingdom":"Bishopsgate, London, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Hampshire, England":"Hampshire, England","England":"England","North Mymms, Hertfordshire, England":"North Mymms, Hertfordshire, England"},"fr":{"–":"Décédée","1449–Male":"1449–Décédé","1478–1527":"1478–1527","1479–1501":"1479–1501","1481–1521":"1481–1521","–Female":"Décédée","1479":"1479","1501":"1501","1478":"1478","1521":"1521","1481":"1481","1527":"1527","1449":"1449","Bishopsgate, London, England, United Kingdom":"Bishopsgate, Londres, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Hampshire, England":"Hampshire, Angleterre","England":"Angleterre","North Mymms, Hertfordshire, England":"North Mymms, Hertfordshire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Elizabeth Troutbeck a eu 